ebates are those over multiculturalism, which Jay takes up in an essay on the impasses of identity politics. In closing, he considers how the field of comparative American cultural studies might be constructed.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 26. Mrz 2024) 0aAmerican literaturexHistory and criticismxTheory, etc. 0aAmerican literaturexStudy and teachingzUnited States. 0aCanon (Literature). 0aCultural pluralismzUnited States. 0aCulture conflictzUnited States. 0aLiterature and societyzUnited States. 0aMulticulturalismzUnited States. 4aEducation & History Of Education. 4aLiterary Studies.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertCornell University Press Archive Pre-2000z978311053617140uhttps://doi.org/10.7591/978150173127340uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781501731273423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781501731273/original  a978-3-11-053617-1  Cornell University Press Archive Pre-2000b2000  aEBA_BACKALL  aEBA_EBACKALL  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_EEBKALL  aEBA_PPALL  aGBV-deGruyter-alles